This paper discusses the development of a big-data-aware artificial intelligent based framework for energy-efficient operations of ultra-dense heterogeneous networks (Ud-HetNets). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of adaptive base station operation, proactive caching, and interference-aware resource allocation, which are techniques related to artificial intelligence and optimization. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for energy conservation, which is related to distributed computing and energy efficiency. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
